{"title_page": "2017 in Mexico", "text_new": "{{Year in Mexico|2017}}\n\nThis is a list of events that happened in [[2017]] in Mexico.\n\n==Incumbents==\n* [[President of Mexico|President]]: [[Enrique Pe\u00f1a Nieto]]\n{{For|the list of governors of the states of Mexico|Category:Lists of governors of States of Mexico}}\n\n==Events==\n*18 January \u2013 [[Colegio Americano del Noreste shooting]]\n*14 March \u2013 A mass grave site of more than 250 people is discovered in Palmas de Abajo, Veracruz.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/investigators-find-more-250-skulls-mexico-graves-n733916|title=Investigators Find More Than 250 skulls in Mexico Graves|last=|first=|date=15 March 2017|website=nbcnews.com|access-date=15 March 2017}}</ref>\n*7 September \u2013 [[2017 Chiapas earthquake|A magnitude 8.1]] [[earthquake]] hit off southern [[Mexico]] coast, 300 injury, 98 people killed, and [[tsunami]] have surrounding warning issue.<ref>http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/09/08/mexico-earthquake-powerful-quake-hits-mexicos-coast-tsunami-waves-reported.html</ref>\n*19 September \u2013 [[2017 Puebla earthquake|A magnitude 7.1 earthquake]] strikes central Mexico, killing more than 200 people.<ref name=\"CNN\">{{cite news |last1=Almasy |first1=Steve |last2=Simon |first2=Darran |date=19 September 2017 |title=Central Mexico earthquake kills dozens, topples buildings |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/09/19/americas/mexico-earthquake/index.html |work=[[CNN]] |accessdate=19 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"reforma\">{{cite news |date=19 September 2017 |title=Mueren 4 tras sismo; caen 29 edificios |url=http://www.reforma.com/aplicacioneslibre/preacceso/articulo/default.aspx?id=1213712&v=5&urlredirect=http://www.reforma.com/aplicaciones/articulo/default.aspx?id=1213712&v=5 |work=[[Reforma]] |accessdate=19 September 2017}}</ref>\n* 10 November \u2014 At 7:25 local time, eruption of [[Popocateptl]] continues.\n\n==Deaths==\n===January===\n[[File:Javier Valdez C\u00e1rdenas.j